HEADWORD: Ptisan
<hw>Ptis"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ptisana</ets>
peeled barley, barley water, Gr. <?/, from <?/ to peel, husk; cf. F.
<ets>ptisane</ets>, <ets>tisane</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
decoction of barley with other ingredients; a farinaceous
drink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An aqueous medicine, containing
little, if any, medicinal agent; a tea or tisane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ptolemaic</ent>⟦br⟧
